reviewText: The absolute WORST MOVIE EVER.  My husband and I spent our time laughing at the movie not with the movie.  We spent most of our time analyzing how anyone with a directors title did not see the serious flaws in this movie.  Robin Givens and Elise Neal must have had to complete some type of community service to be in this film (well below their standards).  Horrible, Horrible, movie.  Stay far far away. And the $16 asking price...please, it was not worth the $1.25 I spent to rent it. A disgrace to movies.

I wish there was an option to give it zero stars because this is what this movie(If you can call it that)deserves. What happen to Robin Givens? I know it's a rough economy, but Jesus!!! come on now. This is the worst acting ever in the history of movies pointblank. There is not one positive thing to say about it. I can't stress enough how this is The WORST movie ever!!!!! Trust me save your dollar because it's not worth a penny.
I did not care for this movie. It was the worst ever. I would not recommend this movie to anyone.

I was completely lost when the janitor asked her to sing in the church and they break out into a sensual dance WTH. It made no sense at all. I hate when these low budget movies use famous actors as the face of their product and they are barely in the movie.
This is another great movie. It came on time and it has a great storyline. The lesson is great for many.
